{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"EPH","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Ephesians"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Paul’s Greeting to the Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../acts/19.htm#8|>Acts 19:8–12</a>; <a href =|../revelation/2.htm|>Revelation 2:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["To the saints   in Ephesus, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some manuscripts do not include <i>in Ephesus</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}," the faithful in Christ Jesus: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Spiritual Blessings"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../romans/8.htm#28|>Romans 8:28–34</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Blessed be the God and Father of our  Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us in Christ with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly realms. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For He chose us in Him before the foundation of the world  to be holy and blameless in His presence . In love ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He predestined us for adoption as His sons   through Jesus Christ, according to the good pleasure of His will, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"to the praise of His glorious grace, which He has freely given us in the Beloved One. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"In Him we have  redemption through His  blood, the forgiveness of our trespasses, according to the riches of His grace ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"that He lavished on us with all wisdom and understanding. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And He has made known to us the mystery of His  will according to His  good pleasure, which He purposed in Christ ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"as a plan for the fullness of time, to bring all things  in  heaven and  on  earth together in  Christ . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"In Him    we were also chosen as God’s own, having been predestined according to the plan of Him who works out  everything by the counsel of His will, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"in order that we, who were the first to hope in  Christ,  would be for the praise of His glory. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And in Him, having heard and believed the word  of truth —  the gospel of your salvation —  you were sealed with the  promised Holy Spirit  , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"who is the pledge of our  inheritance until the redemption of those who are God’s possession, to the praise of His glory. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Spiritual Wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../1_corinthians/2.htm#6|>1 Corinthians 2:6–16</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For this reason , ever since I heard about   your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love  for all the saints, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"I have not stopped giving thanks for you,  remembering you in my  prayers, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"that the God of our  Lord Jesus Christ, the  glorious Father, may give you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in your knowledge of Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"I ask that the eyes of your heart ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR <i>the eyes of your understanding</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"may be enlightened, so that you  may know   the hope of His calling,  the riches of His  glorious inheritance in the saints, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"and  the surpassing greatness of His power to us who believe.  These are  in accordance with the working of His mighty  strength, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"which He exerted in  Christ when He raised Him from the dead and seated Him at His right hand in the heavenly realms, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"far above all rule and authority,  power and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in the present  age but also in the one to come. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And God put everything under His  feet and made Him head over everything for the church, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"which is His  body, the fullness of Him who fills  all in all. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Alive with Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../colossians/2.htm#6|>Colossians 2:6–23</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"And you were dead in your trespasses and  sins, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"in which  you used to walk when you conformed to the ways of this  world and of the ruler of the power of the air, the spirit who is now  at work in the sons  of disobedience. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"All of us also lived among them at one time, fulfilling the cravings of our  flesh and indulging its desires and  thoughts  .   Like the rest, we were by nature children of wrath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But because of His great  love for us  ,  God, who is rich in mercy, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"made us alive with  Christ even when we were dead in our trespasses. It is by grace you have been saved! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And God raised us up with Christ and seated us with Him in the heavenly realms in Christ Jesus, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"in order that in the  coming ages He might display the surpassing riches of His grace, demonstrated by His kindness to us in Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For it is  by grace you have been saved through faith, and this not from yourselves; it is the gift of God, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"not by works, so that no one can boast. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For we are God’s workmanship, created in Christ Jesus to do good works, which  God prepared in advance as our way of life  . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>which God prepared beforehand, that we should walk in them.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>One in Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../philippians/2.htm|>Philippians 2:1–4</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Therefore remember that formerly you who are Gentiles in the flesh  and called uncircumcised by the so-called circumcision (that done in the body by human hands) —  ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"remember that at that time you were separate from Christ, alienated from the commonwealth  of Israel, and strangers to the covenants of the promise, without  hope and without God in the world. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But now in Christ Jesus you who once were far away have been brought near through the blood  of Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For He Himself is our  peace, who has made  the two one and has torn down the dividing  wall  of hostility ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"by abolishing in His  flesh the law  of commandments and decrees.  He did this  to create in Himself one new man out of the two, thus making peace ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"and reconciling  both of them  to God in one body through the cross, by which He put to death their hostility. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}," He came and preached peace to you who were far away and peace to those who were near. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For through Him   we both have  access to the Father by one Spirit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Christ Our Cornerstone"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../isaiah/28.htm#14|>Isaiah 28:14–22</a>; <a href =|../1_corinthians/3.htm#10|>1 Corinthians 3:10–15</a>; <a href =|../1_peter/2.htm|>1 Peter 2:1–8</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Therefore  you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but  fellow citizens with the saints and members of God’s household  , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, with Christ Jesus Himself as the cornerstone. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"In Him the whole building is fitted together and grows into a holy temple in the Lord. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And in Him you too are being built together into a dwelling place  for God in His Spirit. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Mystery of the Gospel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"For this reason  I, Paul, the prisoner  of Christ Jesus for the sake of you  Gentiles... ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["This train of thought is continued in verse 14."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"}," Surely you have heard about the stewardship  of God’s  grace  that was given to me for you, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"that is, the mystery made known to me by revelation, as I have already written  briefly. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"In reading this, then, you will be able to understand my  insight into the mystery  of Christ, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"which  was not made known    to men in other generations as  it has now been revealed by the Spirit to God’s holy apostles and prophets. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"This mystery is that through the gospel the Gentiles are fellow heirs,  fellow members of the body, and fellow partakers of the promise in Christ Jesus. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I became a servant of this gospel by the gift  of God’s  grace,  given me through the working of His power. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Though I am less than the least of all the saints, this  grace was given me: to preach to the Gentiles the unsearchable riches  of Christ, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"and to illuminate for everyone  the stewardship ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>and to illuminate the stewardship</i>; TR <i>and to illuminate for everyone the fellowship</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"of this mystery, which for  ages past was kept hidden in  God, who created  all things. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," His purpose was  that now, through the church, the manifold wisdom  of God should be made known to the rulers and  authorities in the heavenly realms, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"according to  the eternal purpose that He accomplished in  Christ Jesus our  Lord. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"In Him and through  faith in Him ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>through His faithfulness</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"we may enter  God’s  presence  with boldness and  confidence. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So I ask you not to be discouraged because of my  sufferings for you, which are your glory. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Paul’s Prayer for the Ephesians"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"... for this reason  I bow my  knees before the Father, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>before the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"from whom every family in heaven and on earth derives its name. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"I ask that out of the riches of His glory He may strengthen you with power through His  Spirit in your inner being, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"so that Christ may dwell in your  hearts through  faith. Then you, being rooted and grounded in love, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," will have power, together with all the saints, to comprehend  the length and width and height and depth ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"of the love  of Christ, and to know this love that surpasses  knowledge, that you may be filled with all the fullness  of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Now to Him who is able to do immeasurably more than all  we ask or imagine, according to His power that is at work within us, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"to Him be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus throughout all  generations, forever  and ever. Amen. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Unity in the Body"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../psalms/133.htm|>Psalm 133:1–3</a>; <a href =|../1_corinthians/1.htm#10|>1 Corinthians 1:10–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"As a prisoner in the Lord, then, I urge you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling  you have received: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"with all humility and gentleness, with patience, bearing with one another in love, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"and with diligence to preserve the unity of the Spirit through the bond  of peace. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"There is one body and one Spirit, just as  you were called to one hope when you were called; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"one Lord, one faith, one baptism; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"one God and Father of all, who is over all and through all and in all. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Now to each one of us  grace has been given according to the measure of the gift  of Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"This is why it says: ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>He says</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When He ascended on high, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He led captives away, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and gave gifts  to men.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Psalm 68:18"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"}," What does  He ascended” mean, except  that  He also descended ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR <i>except that He also descended first</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"to the lower parts of the earth? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"He who descended is  the very One who ascended above all the heavens, in order to fill  all things. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And it was He who gave some  to be apostles,  some to be prophets,  some to be evangelists, and some to be pastors and teachers, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"  to equip the saints for works of ministry and to build up the body  of Christ, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"until   we all reach   unity in the faith and in the knowledge of the Son  of God,   as we mature to the full measure of the stature  of Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then we will no longer be infants, tossed about by the waves and carried around by every wind  of teaching and by the  clever cunning  of men in their  deceitful scheming. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Instead, speaking the truth in love, we will in all things grow up into Christ Himself, who is the head. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"From Him the whole body, fitted and held together by every  supporting ligament,    grows   and builds itself up  in love through the work   of each individual part. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>New Life in Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../colossians/3.htm|>Colossians 3:1–17</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So I tell you this, and insist on it in the Lord, that you must no longer walk  as the Gentiles do, in the futility of their thinking. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"They are darkened in their understanding and alienated from the life  of God because of the ignorance  that is in them due to the hardness of their hearts. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Having lost all sense of shame, they have given themselves over  to sensuality for the practice of every kind of impurity, with a craving for more. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But this is not the way  you came to know  Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Surely  you heard of Him and were taught in Him— in keeping with the truth that is in  Jesus— ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"to put off your   former way of life, your old self, which is being corrupted by its  deceitful desires; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"}," to be renewed in the spirit of your minds; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"and to put on the new self, created to be like  God in  true righteousness and holiness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Therefore each of you must put off  falsehood and speak truthfully to his  neighbor, for we are all members of one another. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Be angry, yet do not sin.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>“In your anger do not sin.”</i> Psalm 4:4"]}],"caller":"+"},"Do not let the sun set upon  your anger, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"and do not give the devil a foothold. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"He who has been stealing must steal no longer, but  must work, doing  good with his own hands, that he may have something to share with the one in need. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Let no  unwholesome talk come out of your  mouths, but only what is helpful for building up the one in need and bringing grace to those who listen. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And do not grieve the  Holy Spirit  of God, in whom you were sealed for the day of redemption. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Get rid of   all bitterness,  rage and anger,  outcry and slander, along with every form of malice. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"}," Be kind and tenderhearted to one another, forgiving each other just as in Christ  God forgave you. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Imitators of God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Be imitators  of God, therefore, as beloved children, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and walk in love, just as   Christ loved us ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH <i>Christ loved you</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and gave Himself up  for us as  a fragrant  sacrificial offering  to God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"But among you, as is proper among the saints,  there must not be even a hint of sexual immorality, or of any kind of impurity, or of greed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Nor should there be obscenity,  foolish talk, or crude joking, which  are out of character, but rather thanksgiving. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"For of this  you can be sure : No immoral,  impure, or greedy person (that is, an idolater) has any inheritance in the kingdom  of Christ and of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of such things  the wrath of God is coming on the sons  of disobedience. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Therefore do not be partakers with them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Children of Light"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Walk as children of light, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"for the fruit of the light consists in all goodness,  righteousness, and truth. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Test and prove what  pleases the Lord. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"  Have no fellowship with the  fruitless deeds  of darkness, but  rather expose them. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For it is shameful even to mention what the disobedient do   in secret. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"}," But everything exposed by the light becomes visible, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL begins verse 14 after <i>visible,</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"for everything that is illuminated becomes a light itself. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"So it is said: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Wake up, O sleeper, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" rise up from the dead, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and  Christ will shine on you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Pay careful attention, then, to how you walk, not as unwise but as wise, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"redeeming the time, because the days are evil. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Therefore  do not be foolish, but understand what the  Lord’s will is. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"}," Do not get drunk on wine,  which leads to reckless indiscretion. Instead, be filled with the Spirit. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Speak to one another with psalms,  hymns, and spiritual songs. Sing and make music in your hearts to the Lord, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"always giving thanks to God  the Father for everything in the name of our  Lord Jesus Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Wives and Husbands"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../songs/1.htm|>Song of Solomon 1:1–17</a>; <a href =|../1_peter/3.htm|>1 Peter 3:1–7</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Submit to one another out of reverence for Christ. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>in the fear of Christ.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"}," Wives, submit to your husbands as to the Lord. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"For the husband is the head of the wife  as  Christ is the head of the church, His body, of which He is the Savior. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Now as the church submits  to Christ, so also  wives should submit to their husbands in everything. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"}," Husbands, love your wives, just as  Christ loved the church and gave Himself up  for her ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"to sanctify her, cleansing her by the washing  with water through the word, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"and to present her to Himself as a glorious  church,  without stain or wrinkle or any  such blemish, but   holy and blameless. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"In the same way ,  husbands ought to love  their wives as  their own bodies. He who loves his  wife loves himself. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Indeed, no one ever hated his own body, but he nourishes and cherishes it, just as  Christ does the church. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For we are members of His body. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include <i>—of His flesh and of His bones</i>."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"For this reason  a man will leave his father and  mother and be united to his  wife, and the two will become  one flesh.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Genesis 2:24 (see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"This  mystery is profound, but I am speaking about Christ and  the church. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Nevertheless,  each one   of you also  must love his  wife as he loves himself, and the wife  must respect her husband. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Children and Parents"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../colossians/3.htm#18|>Colossians 3:18–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"}," Children, obey your  parents in the Lord, for this is right. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Honor your  father and  mother (which is the first commandment with a promise), ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"that it may go well with you and that you may have a long life on the earth.” ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Exodus 20:12; Deuteronomy 5:16"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"  Fathers, do not provoke your  children to wrath; instead, bring them up  in the discipline and instruction of the Lord. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Serving with Honor"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../colossians/3.htm#22|>Colossians 3:22–25</a>; <a href =|../1_timothy/6.htm|>1 Timothy 6:1–2</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"}," Slaves, obey your earthly  masters with respect and fear and sincerity of  heart, just as  you would obey  Christ. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And do this not only  to please them  while they are watching, but as servants of Christ, doing the will  of God from your heart. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Serve with good will, as to the Lord and not to men, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"because you know that  the Lord  will reward each one  for whatever good he does, whether he is slave or free. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And  masters, do the same  for your slaves. Give up your use of threats, because you know that He who is both their  Master and yours is in heaven, and there is no favoritism with Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Full Armor of God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"}," Finally, be strong in the Lord and in  His  mighty power. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Put on the full armor  of God, so that you  can make your stand against the  devil’s schemes. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For our  struggle is not against flesh and blood, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the powers of this world’s darkness, and against the spiritual forces  of evil in the heavenly realms. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Therefore  take up the full armor  of God, so that when the day  of evil comes, you will be able to stand your ground, and having done everything, to stand. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Stand firm then, with the belt of truth buckled around your  waist, with the breastplate  of righteousness arrayed, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"and with your feet fitted with the readiness of the gospel  of peace. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"In addition to all this, take up the shield  of faith, with which you can extinguish all the flaming  arrows of the evil one. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And take the helmet  of salvation and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Pray in the Spirit at all times, with every kind of prayer and petition.  To this end, stay alert with all perseverance  in your prayers for all the saints. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Pray also for me, that whenever I open  my mouth, words may be given me  so that I will boldly make known the mystery of the gospel, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"for which I am an ambassador in chains. Pray that I may proclaim it fearlessly  , as I should . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Final Greetings"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../philippians/4.htm#21|>Philippians 4:21–23</a>; <a href =|../2_timothy/4.htm#19|>2 Timothy 4:19–22</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful servant in the Lord, will tell you everything,  so that you also may know  about me and what I am doing. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"I have sent him to you for this very purpose, that you may know  about us, and that he may encourage your  hearts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Peace to the brothers and love with faith from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"}," Grace to all who love our  Lord Jesus Christ with an undying love. "]}]}